  <title>Mechanism</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>Mechanism</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Body Text2-Note"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="VariableName-small">Kinematic-chain: </text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Parts</text> connected with <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Joints</text>, with at least one <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Joint</text> connecting a <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Part</text> to the <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Base-Part.</text>&#32;</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">To analyze a <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematic-chain</text>, it must be <text styleclass="VariableName-small">kinematically-defined</text> - with <text styleclass="VariableName-small" style="color:#005000;">Green</text>&#32;<text styleclass="Popup Box2">Part-Outlines</text><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">One <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Kinematic-Chain</text> can have one to any number of <text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Motion-Dimensions</text> - for example a Robot with 2-axes has two Motion-Dimensions.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">Other names are: Mechanism and Linkage.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="SeeAlso-small">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Kinematically-Defined-Chain">kinematically-defined</link>.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
